                <title xml:id="name556-4" xml:lang="en" source="#bib556-1" srophe:tags="#syriaca-headword">Peter the Iberian (text)</title>
                <author role="disputed" xml:lang="fr" source="#bib556-1" ref="http://syriaca.org/person/58">
                    <persName xml:lang="en-x-gedsh">
                        <forename sort="1">Zacharias</forename>
                        <addName type="untagged-title" sort="2">Rhetor</addName>
                    </persName> — <persName xml:lang="syr">
                        <forename sort="1">ܙܟܪܝܐ</forename>
                        <addName type="untagged-title" sort="2">ܡܠܝܠܐ</addName>
                    </persName> (<persName xml:lang="fr">
                        <forename>Zacharie</forename>
                        <addName type="untagged-title">le Rhéteur</addName>
                    </persName>)</author>
                <note xml:lang="en" type="abstract" source="#bib556-3 #bib556-10 #bib556-9">The Syriac text is a fragment that ends with 
                    <quote source="#bib556-10">The account about Peter the Iberian is finished.</quote> 
                It is disputed whether or not this is the remainder of a text from which the Georgian life of Peter the Iberian was translated 
                (see "Ancient Versions" below).</note>
                <note xml:lang="syr" type="explicit" source="#bib556-1">
                    <quote>ܘܗܢܐ ܐܣܪܐ ܕܫܬܩܐ ܡܠܐ ܙܒܢܐ ܢܣܒܘ̣. ܐܝܟܢܐ ܕܒܝܕ ܗܢܐ ܢܬܕܟܘܢ̣. ܘܢܐܠܦܘܢ ܐܝܟ ܕܓܪܝܓܪܝܘܣ ܐܡܿܪ. ܡܫܘܚܬܐ ܕܡܠܬܐ ܘܕܫܬܩܐ܀</quote>
                </note>
                <note xml:lang="fr" type="explicit" source="#bib556-1">
                    <quote>Et ils acceptèrent ce lien du silence temporaire pour grâce à lui se purifier et apprendre, comme dit Grégoire «la mesure de la parole et du silence».</quote>
                </note>
                <note xml:lang="en" type="editions">
                    <bibl source="#bib556-1" xml:id="bib556-5">
                        <author>Brooks, E. W.</author>
                        <title>Vitae Virorum apud monophysitas celeberrimorum I</title>
                        <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/2088"/>
                        <citedRange>Paris-Leipzig, 1907, p. 18</citedRange>
                    </bibl>
                </note>
                <note xml:lang="en" type="MSS" source="#bib556-1">
                    <bibl xml:id="bib556-6">ms Berlin, Königliche Bibliothek, syr. 26 (Sachau 321), f. 105r</bibl>
                </note>
                <note xml:lang="en" type="ancientVersion" source="#bib556-1">
                    <bibl xml:id="bib556-7">
                        <editor xml:lang="ru">Н. Я. Марр</editor>
                        <title xml:lang="ru">Житие Петра Ивера царевича-подвижника и епископа Майумского V века. Грузинский подлинник (Православный Палестинский сборник 47), Санкт-Петербург, 1896</title>
                        <note xml:lang="fr">D’après Tarchnishvili, cette Vita remonte à la Vita écrite par
            Zacharie et non à BHO 955</note>
                        <ptr target="http://syriaca.org/bibl/2072"/>
